TextChange: Often times persons identifying as a \"lone wolf\" can have greater feelings of lonliness, depression, anxiety, and stress, because a percieved lack of community and support can wreck an individual's happiness. These \"lone wolf\" individuals may have high levels of broken trust, leading to refusal or inability to become part of a community. Without having this support system around them to help carry the mental load of simply existing, they can potentially be very unhappy people.
